  <text>
    <body>
      <ab type="lido:objectWorkType">Leaflet</ab>
      <ab subtype="creation" type="lido:event">
        <date>1948 after</date>
      </ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The leaflet features a framed graphic illustration showing a man entering the picture from the right. He is gazing into the distance, wearing a cap resembling a sailor hat and a shirt or jacket. He is holding a flagpole in his right hand; the flagpole and flag exit the image at the top left. The man’s left hand is bandaged. In the lower section of the picture, the Serbo-Croatian translation of the original Russian film title, ‘Третий удар’, is indicated: ‘Treći udar’ (The third strike).</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The legend below the picture gives the name of the film production company, ‘Kiev cinema-studio of art films’, and the year of production (1948). The film was directed by Игорь Савченко (Igor Savchenko). The drawing is in the style of Socialist Realism – the only style of realistic art permitted in the Soviet Union at that time.</ab>
